The Vice President, Mike Pence, delivered remarks at the White House regarding the efforts of President Donald Trump to repeal and replace Obamacare. Pence acknowledged the struggles faced by American families due to skyrocketing premiums and limited choices under Obamacare. He assured the families that help is on the way and that President Trump is fighting for them. Pence urged Republicans in the Senate to act and keep their promise to the American people. The Senate will have the opportunity to begin the debate on a bill to repeal and replace Obamacare. Pence introduced President Trump, who was also present at the event.